parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Damage-Induced Electrical Fire in Seat Adjustment Mechanism
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire caused by water damage to the seat can release toxic fumes, posing a serious health hazard to occupants, and can also lead to a more extensive fire, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.

melted plastic facing on the right side of the seat near the seat adjustment mechanism

doors will not shut unless the owner pulls over and shuts the door from the outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alignment Issues Causing Premature Tire Wear and Transmission Problems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Misaligned wheels can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents. Additionally, misalignment can put excessive stress on the transmission, leading to premature failure.
